    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe OSC 52 implementation writes raw sequences to the TTY to manage the clipboard. This should be abstracted through a clipboard UI interface so that other UIs can also manage the clipboard. The TUI would implement these events using OSC 52, so Nvim core would no longer need to write or read escape sequences directly.\n\nThis would be a fallback/default if no other clipboard provider is available/in use.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNew UI events:\n\nCore to UI:\n\n```\n[\"clipboard_write\", <data>]\n[\"clipboard_read_request\"]\n```\n\nUI to core:\n\n```\n[\"clipboard_read_response\", <data>]\n```",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
